Installation:

0) Install python/django
1) Install everything in the <projectroot>/bin folder
2) Set your ARD_URL in settings.py - the default is set for Berkeley
3) put your campusmap in <projectroot>/site-media/ as campusmap.png
4) add imagemap coords to <projectroot>/templates/campusmap.html
5) Read the deployment instructions below


Before deploying campenport in a publicly-accessible way, please do the following: 

1) set the SECRET_KEY in settings.py in root

2.0) Read the instructions in <projectroot>/database/README_ABOUT_DBs



Continue after 2.0:
2.1) login to the admin interface (http://<rooturl>/admin) with username: defaultadmin and password: default
3) create a new user for yourself and delete the default account

If you do not do this, your database will essentially be PUBLICLY EDITABLE.
